The Firm underwent a strategic reorganization in August of 2015, and today only manages and invests the Firm's own investment capital. nxVenture Capital does not manage nor does it solicit outside investors or investment capital, operating as a "Private Investment Company" as defined by the Investment Company Act of 1940 (as amended).  nxVenture Capital's operating structure is highly unconventional in the financial sector, and resembles a Silicon Valley technology firm more than a conventional investment management company. Even the Firm's office interiors are designed as performance-based holistic workplace environments that include the integration of cutting-edge technology and media to create dynamic spaces that foster innovation and collaboration. nxVenture Capital collaborated on the unique design of their office interiors with Skidmore, Owings & Merrill (SOM), one of the largest and most influential architecture, interior design, engineering, and urban planning firms in the world. nxVenture Capital's business model relies on the Firm's strategic operating foundation as a private investment firm. This affords nxVenture Capital's management much wider latitude operationally than a firm relying on outside investment capital. ability to conduct its investment operating environment. The Firm operates free of the inevitable pressures that are inherent with the common industry model of managing multiple investment funds capitalized by outside investment capital.

Description: SunTech Drive delivers the most efficient off-grid nanogrid controllers on the market.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: SunTech Drive delivers the most efficient off-grid nanogrid controllers on the market.  Their patent pending designs represent a dramatic departure from the large and costly legacy controllers of the past.  They replace legacy electromagnetic cores and windings with high speed digital switching silicon and adaptive firmware.  Not only does this result in controllers that are an order of magnitude smaller and lighter it also allows us to incorporate multiple system components into one integrated controller.    Their devices incorporate a variable frequency drive, MPPT controller, voltage boost and inverter in one tightly integrated offering.  Their use of adaptive firmware allows us to serve as a UNIVERSAL controller.  Today’s core and winding based controllers need to be custom designed and built for each and every pump on the market leading to a complex set of products for customers and distributors alike.  Their adaptive firmware allows our controllers to universally support both single and three phase devices; 50Hz and 60Hz; 120, 230 and 380V, etc.

Full Description: McKennon Law Group PC is the San Diego law firm, also known as San Diego Insurance Claims Lawyer, with attorneys who fight insurance companies. Our insurance attorneys handle claims for clients that need to get their well-deserved insurance benefits. With a legal team made up of former claim denial litigation attorneys, our law firm works to bring aggressive and experienced representation for our clients.  We founded McKennon Law Group PC for one purpose: to provide you with targeted, highly effective representation geared to pursue the best possible results. Our single-minded focus is on promptly and efficiently achieving the results you deserve. Our firm assists individuals and businesses in their insurance disputes, and we have aggressively fought numerous insurance companies and third-party administrators (TPAs) on behalf of our clients. Insurance companies hate to see the McKennon Law Group PC fighting their insureds’ claims because there are few firms that bring more experience, skill and an aggressive style to the insurance claim litigation table.  As a nationally recognized law firm with an extensive understanding of the insurance industry, the attorneys at McKennon Law Group PC have provided effective and reliable legal representation to clients since 1986. We limit our practice areas to insurance, insurance bad faith and ERISA claims and litigation so that we can focus on our clients’ denied insurance and ERISA claims. Our practice areas include insurance bad faith claims, disability insurance claims, life insurance and annuities claims, ERISA benefit claims, Accidental Death and Dismemberment Claims, Health Insurance Claims, Long-Term Care Claims, and professional liability insurance claims.  Led by founding attorney Robert J. McKennon. Among the most respected insurance litigators in California and in the United States, Mr. McKennon has been named to the Super Lawyers list every year since 2011. He and his firm have received numerous other awards and recognitions, including top insurance attorney and insurance law firm in California and in the United States. We focus on our clients, while also focusing on getting results.
